  "prompt": "Which type of questions in asp.net practical interview?",
  "response": "In an ASP.NET practical interview, you can expect a mix of general questions about the framework, coding challenges, and scenario-based questions. Here\u2019s a broad list of the types of questions often asked in practical interviews:\n\n### 1. **Conceptual Questions**\n- Explain the difference between ASP.NET Web Forms and ASP.NET MVC.\n- What is ASP.NET Core? How does it differ from previous versions of ASP.NET?\n- Describe the ASP.NET page lifecycle.\n- What are the main components of the ASP.NET MVC architecture?\n- Explain the differences between server-side and client-side controls.\n\n### 2. **Coding Challenges**\n- Write a simple CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) application in ASP.NET MVC.\n- Implement custom validation for a form in ASP.NET.\n- Create an API using ASP.NET Web API that performs basic operations on a database.\n- Write a function to query data from a database and display it in a table.\n- Create a simple login/logout functionality using ASP.NET Identity.\n\n### 3. **Scenario-Based Questions**\n- How would you handle user authentication and authorization in your application?\n- Discuss how you would manage state in a web application.\n- If you were to optimize an ASP.NET application for performance, what strategies would you use?\n- How would you implement caching in ASP.NET?\n- Describe how you would implement error handling in an ASP.NET application.\n\n### 4. **Technical Questions**\n- What are Razor views, and how do you use them?\n- Explain the purpose of Model-View-Controller (MVC) pattern in ASP.NET.\n- Discuss dependency injection. How do you implement it in ASP.NET Core?\n- What is middleware in ASP.NET Core, and can you provide examples?\n- How do routing and endpoint mapping work in ASP.NET Core?\n\n### 5. **Front-end Integration**\n- How do you integrate JavaScript libraries with an ASP.NET application?\n- Explain how to use AJAX in an ASP.NET application.\n- How would you implement responsive design in your ASP.NET application?\n  \n### 6. **Testing and Debugging**\n- Describe your approach to testing an ASP.NET application.\n- What tools do you use for debugging ASP.NET applications?\n- Can you explain how to write unit tests for an ASP.NET controller?\n\n### 7. **Security**\n- What security features are available in ASP.NET?\n- How would you prevent SQL injection in your applications?\n- Discuss Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF) and how to protect against it in ASP.NET.\n\nPreparing for these topics will help you perform better in an ASP.NET practical interview. It's also good to have hands-on experience and be ready to demonstrate your coding skills in real-time.",
